01:01:31.750 --> 01:01:34.650
It's just too damn good
to talk about, heh.

01:01:35.290 --> 01:01:38.620
Well, I'm not too proud of it.

01:01:38.790 --> 01:01:41.560
Good pictures are always of the dead
and the wounded.

01:01:43.760 --> 01:01:47.360
You know,
I like the war in your book better.

01:01:48.300 --> 01:01:51.900
You said
what we all think about women

01:01:52.070 --> 01:01:56.600
- and never have the guts to tell them.
- God bless you, sir, heh.

01:01:56.980 --> 01:01:58.500
- Here's to telling them.
- Yeah.

01:01:58.680 --> 01:02:02.110
- Over and over.
- And over, and over, and over, heh.

01:02:05.780 --> 01:02:07.220
Do you know what women do
in Africa?

01:02:08.850 --> 01:02:09.850
What?

01:02:10.820 --> 01:02:15.730
They wear a bone in their nose
and they listen to their men!

01:02:16.360 --> 01:02:19.490
And if they don't listen, they have
to wear another bone in their nose.

01:02:19.660 --> 01:02:23.570
Heh, that's only for two bones
in their... Every woman, two.

01:02:25.840 --> 01:02:29.240
And then they crawl off,
see, to their little thatched huts

01:02:29.410 --> 01:02:32.500
and have their damn babies
and they crawl right back

01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:35.080
and pick cocoa nuts
for their husbands.

01:02:35.250 --> 01:02:39.910
Excellent. Excellent.
Proper division of marital duties.

01:02:41.320 --> 01:02:44.380
Do you know what women are doing
in this country, huh?

01:02:44.560 --> 01:02:47.790
They're plotting
to take over the world.

01:02:47.960 --> 01:02:53.800
They're sneakily outliving men
so that they can inherit everything.

01:02:53.970 --> 01:02:59.800
- It's a war, I tell you.
- You are absolutely right.

01:03:00.640 --> 01:03:03.230
It's all so clear to me now.

01:03:06.980 --> 01:03:07.980
Hey.

01:03:11.350 --> 01:03:13.550
- What is that you are doing?
- Shh, shh.

01:03:13.720 --> 01:03:17.280
I'm drawing women
as they really are.

01:03:17.460 --> 01:03:20.580
- Is that a woman?
- Well, what does it look like?

01:03:21.860 --> 01:03:23.420
It looks like a horse.

01:03:26.160 --> 01:03:29.970
Right. We'll make that a horse

01:03:30.130 --> 01:03:35.700
and then we'll draw a woman
riding him, it.

01:03:36.340 --> 01:03:38.500
- Good luck.
- Uh...

01:03:39.940 --> 01:03:47.220
Uh, there's a horse.
And a disgusting woman riding him.

01:03:50.560 --> 01:03:53.490
You know, your horses
look as disgusting as your women.

01:03:53.660 --> 01:03:55.460
Thank you, heh.

01:04:04.340 --> 01:04:06.960
Did you see that? Huh?

01:04:07.140 --> 01:04:10.340
- See what?
- One of those women moved.

01:04:14.280 --> 01:04:16.440
Grab the muskets!

01:04:24.920 --> 01:04:25.980
Here they come!

01:04:28.730 --> 01:04:31.420
Don't shoot
till you see the whites of their eyes.

01:04:35.500 --> 01:04:38.960
- Oh, my goodness.
- Duck, huh.

01:04:39.140 --> 01:04:41.130
They're everywhere.
They're all over the place!

01:04:42.510 --> 01:04:45.030
No, you don't.

01:04:53.620 --> 01:04:55.880
They're dropping leaflets!

01:04:58.420 --> 01:05:01.190
Leaflets, hell,
they're bills from Bergdorf's.

01:05:01.360 --> 01:05:04.490
My God, have they no mercy?
Do something. Do something!

01:05:04.660 --> 01:05:09.290
We'll fight them from the beaches,
fight them from the shores,

01:05:09.470 --> 01:05:14.060
and fight them from the...
Ah! My rear!

01:05:16.310 --> 01:05:18.000
- Do me a favor!
- Yeah?

01:05:18.180 --> 01:05:19.870
- Cover me, will you?
- I got you.

01:05:20.040 --> 01:05:23.810
- I got you, mate, I got you.
- Reinforcements.

01:05:23.980 --> 01:05:27.750
- What are you doing?
- Drawing somebody on our side.

01:05:35.990 --> 01:05:38.620
Ah! Your turn. Now it's your turn.

01:05:39.200 --> 01:05:40.500
Blend, blend, blend.

01:05:40.670 --> 01:05:45.600
You're liquefied!
I hope that's blood, blood.

01:05:47.340 --> 01:05:51.710
- Well, I got mine. Do something.
- I'm drawing as fast as I can.

01:05:51.880 --> 01:05:55.110
Uh, well, draw somebody that knows
what they're doing in a battle.

01:05:55.280 --> 01:05:56.650
For instance?

01:05:56.810 --> 01:05:57.870
Try Moshe Dayan.

01:05:59.150 --> 01:06:00.380
Good thinking.

01:06:06.990 --> 01:06:09.650
They're weakening. Attack.

01:06:13.030 --> 01:06:15.760
- Shalom.
- Shalom.

01:06:18.640 --> 01:06:20.400
Watch out!

01:06:22.940 --> 01:06:25.410
Got one. Got two.

01:06:25.580 --> 01:06:29.670
Dirty rotten spies.
Keep up the good work!

01:06:29.850 --> 01:06:32.040
Listen, my children,

01:06:32.220 --> 01:06:39.120
and you shall hear
the Midnight Ride of Paul Revere.

01:06:39.290 --> 01:06:40.490
Peter.

01:06:42.630 --> 01:06:46.720
- Peter!
- Huh? What?

01:06:46.900 --> 01:06:48.660
Aren't you coming up to bed?

01:06:50.100 --> 01:06:53.230
Oh, no, you don't.
That's how you got me the first time.

01:08:36.740 --> 01:08:37.740
What?

01:08:50.760 --> 01:08:53.160
Ahem, hello.

01:09:02.200 --> 01:09:03.399
Hello.

01:09:06.200 --> 01:09:08.069
Just a minute.

01:09:08.240 --> 01:09:11.470
It's for you. It's long distance.

01:09:11.640 --> 01:09:15.439
- I wonder who it could be.
- Not you, it's for your father.

01:09:15.609 --> 01:09:16.640
Which one?

01:09:16.810 --> 01:09:19.810
Don't start that again.
It's for your father.

01:09:21.189 --> 01:09:22.880
Wake up! Long distance!

01:09:23.050 --> 01:09:24.960
- Yeah, yeah. What?
- Cost money.

01:09:25.120 --> 01:09:28.149
- Yeah, yeah. Where? Where?
- Look up. It costs money.

01:09:28.330 --> 01:09:32.560
I got it, I got it. Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.
Hello, yeah.

01:09:32.729 --> 01:09:36.330
Yeah, this is Kozlenko
or what's left of him.

01:09:36.500 --> 01:09:39.899
All right, what? You'll have to speak
louder, I got a bad connection.

01:09:41.609 --> 01:09:43.840
I got a bad connection
inside my head.

01:09:44.010 --> 01:09:47.170
I just... I can't see a thing.
Has anybody seen my glasses?

01:09:47.340 --> 01:09:48.640
You're wearing them.

01:09:48.810 --> 01:09:51.080
Find me a pencil
and take this down, will you?

01:09:51.250 --> 01:09:54.620
Yeah,
my secretary's standing by here.

01:09:54.790 --> 01:09:57.950
Yeah, when? This afternoon?

01:09:58.120 --> 01:10:02.030
- Oh, my...
- Yeah, my passport's okay.

01:10:02.190 --> 01:10:04.660
But I, uh, do need a visa
for the little guy

01:10:04.830 --> 01:10:07.490
that is hammering away
at my temples, heh.

01:10:16.710 --> 01:10:20.800
Peter, for chrissake, you got a pencil?

01:10:20.980 --> 01:10:25.940
I gotta catch a plane someplace,
somewhere. Yeah. Yeah, ahem.

01:10:26.750 --> 01:10:29.350
Yeah, all right, yeah.
All right, go slow, will you?

01:10:29.520 --> 01:10:32.120
My assistant, uh,
doesn't take shorthand.

01:10:32.290 --> 01:10:38.590
Yeah, yeah, Kennedy Airport,
Air China, flight 409.

01:10:39.330 --> 01:10:40.350
You got that?

01:10:42.030 --> 01:10:43.730
I think so.

01:10:43.900 --> 01:10:45.630
Sure, sure, I'm ready to leave.

01:10:45.800 --> 01:10:48.710
As a matter of fact,
I was going to anyway.

01:10:48.870 --> 01:10:52.070
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:10:52.240 --> 01:10:53.480
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:10:53.610 --> 01:10:56.340
I hope you men are proud
of what you did last night.

01:10:56.510 --> 01:10:59.750
We don't deserve all the credit.
Moshe Dayan turned the tide.

01:10:59.920 --> 01:11:01.010
- Who?
- Yeah.

01:11:01.190 --> 01:11:03.150
Twelve-thirty in the afternoon,
you got that?

01:11:03.320 --> 01:11:04.340
I think so.

01:11:04.520 --> 01:11:06.750
Okay, give me that pad, will you?

01:11:08.860 --> 01:11:09.880
Jesus.

01:11:11.030 --> 01:11:13.000
You're in worse shape than I am.

01:11:13.160 --> 01:11:15.900
Don't worry, I'm gonna take the train
into the city with you.

01:11:16.070 --> 01:11:17.560
I've got it committed to memory.

01:11:17.740 --> 01:11:19.360
Where are you going?

01:11:19.540 --> 01:11:22.840
Uh, I have to speak to Howard Mann
about the new book.

01:11:23.010 --> 01:11:24.100
He's been screaming at me.

01:11:24.280 --> 01:11:27.310
You better get cleaned up, unless
you're thinking of taking a freight train.

01:11:27.410 --> 01:11:30.870
- Yeah, all right.
- Yeah, cleaned up. Yeah.

01:11:32.020 --> 01:11:34.420
Ugh, here, the stairs are this way.

01:11:34.590 --> 01:11:35.610
I'm new here.

01:11:35.790 --> 01:11:36.810
Good mornings, Daddy.

01:11:36.990 --> 01:11:38.650
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:11:44.360 --> 01:11:50.270
Mother, there's dead women
all over the walls.

01:11:52.070 --> 01:11:54.660
Why would men draw
things like that?

01:11:54.840 --> 01:11:57.140
It's the only way they can win.

01:12:08.890 --> 01:12:12.650
Two tomato juices with the raw egg
and here's your Tabasco sauce.

01:12:12.820 --> 01:12:14.740
- Thank you.
- Will there be anything else, sir?

01:12:14.930 --> 01:12:18.890
A short prayer. Excuse me.

01:12:25.070 --> 01:12:28.400
- Here's a little salvation for you.
- Thank you.

01:12:33.340 --> 01:12:36.640
You know, it's not easy
leaving them like that.

01:12:37.950 --> 01:12:40.080
I can still see their faces.

01:12:40.250 --> 01:12:44.590
David, Linda, looking up at me.

01:12:44.760 --> 01:12:48.320
Caroline growing up, mature, firm.

01:12:48.490 --> 01:12:51.890
Woman. And Terry.

01:12:52.730 --> 01:12:54.860
Heh, you know,
there's always a little something

01:12:55.030 --> 01:12:57.090
between a man and a woman
who bore his children.

01:12:57.270 --> 01:12:59.430
I know you understand that.

01:12:59.600 --> 01:13:02.270
I know you don't begrudge me
a few memories

01:13:02.440 --> 01:13:07.280
to keep me company in the darkness
and heat and loneliness of the jungle.

01:13:07.440 --> 01:13:09.110
You're full of crap, Steven.

01:13:09.280 --> 01:13:11.940
- I beg your pardon?
- You're out and you're glad you're out.

01:13:12.120 --> 01:13:13.140
What do you mean?

01:13:13.320 --> 01:13:15.450
You've got a daughter
who doesn't listen to anybody,

01:13:15.620 --> 01:13:19.150
another one who stammers and a son
who can only sleep in front of doors.

01:13:19.320 --> 01:13:20.720
You've loused up a whole family.

01:13:20.890 --> 01:13:23.020
Say, how would you like a belt
in the nose?

01:13:23.190 --> 01:13:25.390
- I wouldn't.
- Heh, damn right.

01:13:25.560 --> 01:13:27.690
A father is supposed
to stay at home.

01:13:27.870 --> 01:13:31.270
He doesn't just breeze
through scattering presents

01:13:31.440 --> 01:13:33.670
and singing songs
like a goddamn wood nymph.

01:13:34.710 --> 01:13:36.470
- I think you mean satyr.
- That's right.

01:13:36.640 --> 01:13:40.270
A wood nymph has breasts.
At least the ones I've seen.

01:13:40.440 --> 01:13:42.310
And ivy growing out of their hair.

01:13:42.480 --> 01:13:44.640
Well, you think I don't know
why you came back?

01:13:44.820 --> 01:13:47.680
Because when you found out that
Terry was marrying somebody else,

01:13:47.850 --> 01:13:49.410
it turned you on.

01:13:52.690 --> 01:13:55.090
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:13:56.860 --> 01:13:58.950
Yeah, it did, actually.

01:13:59.130 --> 01:14:02.590
Penn Station.
Pennsylvania Station.

01:14:02.770 --> 01:14:05.170
You're just not cut out
for this kind of life, Steven.

01:14:05.340 --> 01:14:06.980
Go back and forth
to an office every day.

01:14:07.140 --> 01:14:09.330
You'd lose your mind
before your transfers ran out.

01:14:09.510 --> 01:14:11.530
I suppose you don't feel
that way sometimes?

01:14:11.710 --> 01:14:14.180
- Sometimes.
- You should be the first to understand.

01:14:17.150 --> 01:14:19.550
- Uh, Steven.
- What?

01:14:19.720 --> 01:14:22.520
Yeah. Uh, these glasses
make my headache worse

01:14:22.690 --> 01:14:24.760
and I can't see without them.
Would you help me out?

01:14:24.860 --> 01:14:28.590
I'm not seeing too well
myself today. Uh, hang on.

01:14:28.760 --> 01:14:31.190
Maybe we can make it together.

01:14:36.270 --> 01:14:38.630
- Steve?
- Yeah.

01:14:38.800 --> 01:14:41.030
I think you ought to give your kids
a break.

01:14:41.210 --> 01:14:44.660
Stop playing on them like they
were violins, let them get over you.

01:14:44.840 --> 01:14:47.140
- Terry too?
- She's over you.

01:14:47.310 --> 01:14:49.470
- Are you sure?
- Positive.

01:14:49.650 --> 01:14:52.810
I believe you. I believe you
and I respect your opinion.

01:14:52.980 --> 01:14:54.980
- But are you sure?
- Absolutely.

01:14:55.150 --> 01:14:58.680
Christ, I'll be upset for weeks over this,
I guarantee you.

01:15:05.200 --> 01:15:06.720
Damn women.

01:15:07.560 --> 01:15:12.370
Hot pants, miniskirts, no brassieres,
why can't they leave us alone?

01:15:13.340 --> 01:15:15.640
There's a cab, uh,
you think you can make it all right?

01:15:15.810 --> 01:15:18.780
- Yeah. Where you going?
- I gotta tell her what I think of her

01:15:18.940 --> 01:15:20.880
and my plane leaves at 12:30, heh.

01:15:21.040 --> 01:15:23.520
There's... Uh, you're sure
you can make it all right now, huh?

01:15:23.620 --> 01:15:26.280
I'm fine. Just don't kiss me goodbye.

01:15:33.420 --> 01:15:35.620
750 Madison.

01:15:40.960 --> 01:15:43.090
When did you first feel the pain?

01:15:43.270 --> 01:15:45.860
This morning. Maybe last night.

01:15:46.040 --> 01:15:49.370
Everything about last night
is understandably vague.

01:15:50.210 --> 01:15:54.800
The condition is acute.
There's gonna have to be an operation.

01:15:55.410 --> 01:15:57.810
- Do you appreciate frankness?
- Yes.

01:15:57.980 --> 01:16:01.710
What I don't appreciate is people who
say, "Do you appreciate frankness?"

01:16:04.520 --> 01:16:09.430
- There's less than a fifty-fifty chance.
- Of what?

01:16:09.590 --> 01:16:12.290
That you'll ever see anything.

01:16:14.230 --> 01:16:16.600
Well, at least
I won't have to watch television.

01:16:16.770 --> 01:16:21.170
- Want me to call your wife?
- Uh, no.

01:16:22.110 --> 01:16:23.400
You're not going home, you know.

01:16:23.570 --> 01:16:27.070
I want you in the hospital tonight
and we'll operate in the morning.

01:16:28.280 --> 01:16:30.870
Well, in that case,
maybe I better call.

01:16:34.320 --> 01:16:36.550
Would you dial an operator for me?

01:16:39.720 --> 01:16:43.680
Peter? Do you know
what you're gonna say?

01:16:43.860 --> 01:16:46.090
Mm-hm. Let's have lunch.

01:16:51.170 --> 01:16:52.900
I don't know
what you're trying to explain to me.

01:16:53.000 --> 01:16:55.960
- Let go of my arm.
- I can't let go. That's what.

01:16:56.140 --> 01:16:57.660
- Why?
- I might fall down.

01:16:57.840 --> 01:16:59.430
We haven't even had
our first martini.

01:16:59.610 --> 01:17:03.070
It's my eyes. The doctor says
I have to have an operation on my eyes.

01:17:03.250 --> 01:17:05.370
- Your eyes?
- That's why I want you to talk to Terry

01:17:05.480 --> 01:17:07.310
- at lunch, huh?
- Operation?

01:17:07.480 --> 01:17:10.850
I may go blind.
Easy, Howard. Are you okay?

01:17:12.220 --> 01:17:13.250
I almost fainted.

01:17:13.420 --> 01:17:16.380
If I had known you were gonna take it
that hard, I wouldn't have told you.

01:17:16.560 --> 01:17:18.560
Suppose it was a mistake, huh?
See another doctor.

01:17:18.760 --> 01:17:21.960
I've seen another doctor
and there's no mistake.

01:17:22.130 --> 01:17:23.620
It's always the good guys.

01:17:23.800 --> 01:17:26.100
Howard, stop it. You gotta go in there
and speak to her.

01:17:26.270 --> 01:17:27.670
- Yeah, I'm sorry.
- You all right?

01:17:27.800 --> 01:17:31.100
Yeah. I'm all right now.

01:17:31.280 --> 01:17:34.770
Now, remember, I don't want her
to know anything about this.

01:17:34.950 --> 01:17:37.140
You've got so much courage,
I'm goddamn awed.

01:17:37.310 --> 01:17:38.630
- That's very well put.
- Thanks.

01:17:38.820 --> 01:17:41.510
Now, you're to tell her
that you gotta lock me up

01:17:41.690 --> 01:17:43.310
- Watch it.
- for a week

01:17:43.490 --> 01:17:44.890
in order to finish the book.

01:17:45.060 --> 01:17:47.460
There's to be no phone calls
and no visitors.

01:17:47.620 --> 01:17:49.320
- Careful.
- Okay.

01:17:49.490 --> 01:17:51.690
And she's not to try to contact me.
You got it?

01:17:51.860 --> 01:17:56.600
- Uh-huh. Got it.
- Howard, if you betray me on this,

01:17:56.770 --> 01:17:58.600
I'm gonna beat you to death
with my white cane

01:17:58.700 --> 01:18:01.370
and feed your remains to my dog.

01:18:02.940 --> 01:18:04.600
I'm ready.

01:18:09.980 --> 01:18:18.790
Well, uh, Terry, the problem is...
Actually, that lazy husband of yours

01:18:18.960 --> 01:18:21.650
- owes me a book.
- Howard, heh.

01:18:21.830 --> 01:18:23.990
- And you're crying about it?
- Well, you know Howard,

01:18:24.090 --> 01:18:26.360
he gets upset
whenever money is involved.

01:18:26.530 --> 01:18:27.850
- Let's cheer up, Howard.
- Yeah.

01:18:28.030 --> 01:18:29.690
Let's all have a drink.
Waiter. Waiter?

01:18:29.870 --> 01:18:31.460
- Yes, sir.
- Three double martinis.

01:18:31.640 --> 01:18:33.040
- I'll have the same.
- Forget his.

01:18:33.200 --> 01:18:35.140
Pull yourself together, huh, Howard.

01:18:35.310 --> 01:18:37.430
And don't worry about the book,
I'll get it finished.

01:18:38.110 --> 01:18:42.710
Now, uh, love, Howard, uh...

01:18:42.880 --> 01:18:45.720
He wants to lock me up at his place
on the Cape until the book is done.

01:18:45.850 --> 01:18:49.010
- Isn't that right, Howard?
- That's right. The book.

01:18:49.850 --> 01:18:51.290
He promised me
that book a month ago

01:18:51.390 --> 01:18:53.350
and I'm gonna lock him up
and throw away the key,

01:18:53.460 --> 01:18:54.980
so you won't be seeing him
for a week.

01:18:55.090 --> 01:18:56.120
- Right?
- Right.

01:18:56.290 --> 01:18:57.660
That's right, Howard.

01:18:58.430 --> 01:19:01.800
So don't worry about him because
that's where's he's gonna be.

01:19:01.970 --> 01:19:03.990
Locked up in my cabin in Cape Cod.

01:19:04.170 --> 01:19:06.250
Don't phone him.
He'll phone you when it's all over.

01:19:06.400 --> 01:19:07.840
Nothing's gonna happen to him

01:19:08.010 --> 01:19:10.530
because all he's gonna be doing
is finishing the goddamn book.

01:19:10.710 --> 01:19:12.440
Well, it'll be pretty tough on me,

01:19:12.610 --> 01:19:14.280
but if that's the way you want it,
Howard.

01:19:14.380 --> 01:19:18.320
You're lying, lying, lying.
Both of you are lying.

01:19:18.480 --> 01:19:19.540
Lying, me?

01:19:19.720 --> 01:19:22.750
You'd never make such a big deal about
going away to work for a week, Peter.

01:19:22.850 --> 01:19:24.250
Me? What...? Of course, I would.

01:19:24.420 --> 01:19:26.650
God, what a suspicious animal
the female is.

01:19:26.820 --> 01:19:28.820
You'd assume
we were with two broads.

01:19:28.990 --> 01:19:31.090
- Are you?
- Maybe.

01:19:32.300 --> 01:19:35.790
- Is he?
- No, no, there are no women. No.

01:19:35.970 --> 01:19:38.330
- He's going to Cape Cod.
- Yeah.

01:19:38.500 --> 01:19:40.300
- God, I can't stand it any longer.
- Howard.

01:19:40.440 --> 01:19:41.460
I'm gonna tell her.

01:19:41.640 --> 01:19:43.400
Howard, you son of a bitch,
you promised me.

01:19:43.510 --> 01:19:45.150
I don't care.
Your courage makes me sick.

01:19:45.280 --> 01:19:47.110
- Howard, please!
- She's got a right to know.

01:19:47.210 --> 01:19:49.090
- Your husband's going blind.
- Howard, please.

01:19:49.210 --> 01:19:51.130
Now look what you've done,
you've shattered her.

01:19:51.250 --> 01:19:53.620
- Howard, blow your nose.
- Thank you.

01:19:53.780 --> 01:19:55.220
May I have another drink, Peter?

01:19:55.390 --> 01:19:57.950
Be careful. Those things are dynamite
on an empty stomach.

01:19:58.120 --> 01:19:59.380
- Shut up, Howard.
- I'm fine.

01:19:59.560 --> 01:20:02.860
Look, love, please try to understand
there was no point in telling you

01:20:03.030 --> 01:20:06.260
- before it was all over with.
- I know about your eyes, Peter.

01:20:08.630 --> 01:20:11.360
- What does that mean?
- I've always known

01:20:11.540 --> 01:20:14.130
from the beginning.
Dr. Harris told me the first day.

01:20:15.670 --> 01:20:20.240
- You mean you married me knowing?
- Jesus, what guts. What devotion.

01:20:20.410 --> 01:20:22.680
- Shut up, Howard.
- Shut up, Howard.

01:20:22.850 --> 01:20:25.080
You mean that you married me
pitying me?

01:20:25.250 --> 01:20:27.380
- I never pitied you.
- You hypocrite.

01:20:27.550 --> 01:20:30.180
For God's sakes, be sensible.

01:20:30.350 --> 01:20:32.410
You went to bed with me
feeling sorry for me.

01:20:32.590 --> 01:20:36.030
I went to bed with you because
I enjoyed going to bed with you.

01:20:36.190 --> 01:20:38.910
And because I thought you'd make
a wonderful father for my children.

01:20:39.030 --> 01:20:41.560
Caroline, Linda and they...
Don't tell me they know.

01:20:41.730 --> 01:20:43.100
- Of course they know.
- My God.

01:20:43.270 --> 01:20:45.470
How could they help
but know the way you fumble around,

01:20:45.570 --> 01:20:46.590
how could they help?

01:20:46.770 --> 01:20:48.410
Goddamn it,
being pitied by a 6-year-old.

01:20:48.540 --> 01:20:50.100
- A baby.
- Shut up and sit down.

01:20:50.270 --> 01:20:51.910
This is a moment
you should share alone...

01:20:52.040 --> 01:20:53.360
- Shut up!
- You sent Steven away

01:20:53.480 --> 01:20:56.240
because you felt it was your duty
to be near your poor blind husband.

01:20:56.350 --> 01:20:58.010
- Let me out.
- Sit down and shut up.

01:20:58.180 --> 01:21:00.950
- Steven went away. He always goes.
- He'll be back. He promised.

01:21:01.120 --> 01:21:03.840
He also left a little innuendo
that you and he and maybe a little...

01:21:03.950 --> 01:21:08.260
For God's sakes. Stop that now.
I don't give a damn about Steven.

01:21:08.430 --> 01:21:10.360
- You're lying.
- Peter.

01:21:10.530 --> 01:21:13.960
You're like all the rest of the women.
You're basically a liar, you're dishonest,

01:21:14.130 --> 01:21:18.730
and you're patronizing and you can't
wait to get a charity case to adopt!

01:21:22.410 --> 01:21:24.970
I don't understand what happened
to you brave, wonderful people.

01:21:25.080 --> 01:21:28.200
Let's get the hell out of here, shall we?
Before that broad comes back

01:21:28.380 --> 01:21:30.400
and starts pitying me
because she ruined my suit.

01:21:30.580 --> 01:21:34.180
Peter. Peter, wait a second.
Wait a second. I'll call her. I'll explain.

01:21:34.350 --> 01:21:37.190
You do, Howard, and I'll kill you.

01:21:40.960 --> 01:21:42.020
Howard?

01:21:44.590 --> 01:21:47.190
Peter. Peter.

01:21:49.570 --> 01:21:52.170
Peter. Peter.

01:21:55.010 --> 01:21:58.010
Howard. Howard.

01:21:58.810 --> 01:22:01.870
Hold still, Peter, it's time.

01:22:02.050 --> 01:22:03.340
For what?

01:22:03.510 --> 01:22:05.680
I'm gonna remove the bandage.

01:22:06.520 --> 01:22:10.150
- Just like that? No trumpets?
- That may come later.

01:22:10.320 --> 01:22:13.450
Easy now. Don't move your head.

01:22:14.120 --> 01:22:16.320
Just relax.

01:22:17.890 --> 01:22:20.760
So far so good, keep going.

01:22:21.530 --> 01:22:23.090
That's it.

01:22:23.870 --> 01:22:25.730
Twelve hundred bucks for this?

01:22:25.900 --> 01:22:27.630
I'm afraid so.

01:22:27.800 --> 01:22:31.610
- What's it like?
- Well, not so deep as a well,

01:22:31.780 --> 01:22:36.340
nor so wide as a barn,
but it will serve.

01:22:36.880 --> 01:22:38.940
Can you distinguish anything?

01:22:39.120 --> 01:22:42.520
Yeah, bright light.

01:22:43.590 --> 01:22:45.520
Some color.

01:22:47.960 --> 01:22:52.290
Few shadows. One of them,
I guess, is you over there.

01:22:53.130 --> 01:22:56.430
- It's me.
- Chrissake, is she here?

01:22:56.600 --> 01:22:57.860
- Peter, don't...
- I told you.

01:22:58.030 --> 01:23:00.900
- Peter, don't get excited.
- Excited? I've been violated.

01:23:01.070 --> 01:23:02.100
I'll leave you two alone.

01:23:02.270 --> 01:23:04.370
- Where are you going?
- I have other patients.

01:23:04.540 --> 01:23:07.380
Well, God help them.

01:23:12.020 --> 01:23:15.610
- Why did you come?
- I was worried about you.

01:23:15.790 --> 01:23:17.650
- Perfectly natural.
- Heh, perfectly.

01:23:17.820 --> 01:23:19.920
Women always worry
about helpless men.

01:23:20.090 --> 01:23:22.580
And small puppies
and donkeys too old to pull carts.

01:23:22.760 --> 01:23:24.920
Don't you think
you can pull a cart anymore?

01:23:25.100 --> 01:23:27.830
Certainly I can over a cliff
or in front of a truck.

01:23:28.000 --> 01:23:29.930
What's the matter with you?

01:23:31.430 --> 01:23:34.340
Don't you realize you'd be better off
with somebody else now?

01:23:36.310 --> 01:23:37.970
Like Steven, for example?

01:23:38.140 --> 01:23:41.840
He's got a lot more substance
than you ever gave him credit for.

01:23:42.010 --> 01:23:47.640
The two of you had something.
You know, both of you and the kids.

01:23:47.820 --> 01:23:49.480
We'd never match that.

01:23:49.650 --> 01:23:53.220
- You'd send me back to Steven?
- I wouldn't stand in your way.

01:23:53.390 --> 01:23:56.490
- I want you to know that. Mm-hm.
- Well, that's very unselfish of you.

01:23:56.660 --> 01:23:58.900
- Noble and fine and good.
- What does all of that mean?

01:23:59.100 --> 01:24:03.530
And after I leave, you get nailed to
an eye chart, burned in your pajamas.

01:24:03.700 --> 01:24:05.500
And we build a new religion
around you.

01:24:06.700 --> 01:24:10.470
- That's not very nice.
- You have a wife and three children.

01:24:10.640 --> 01:24:13.610
You're using this to get out of it,
that's not very nice either.

01:24:13.780 --> 01:24:16.110
I am being practical and objective.

01:24:17.510 --> 01:24:19.680
I cannot go back to him.

01:24:20.280 --> 01:24:26.050
As you said or I think you said, you've
had three kids together, it's no big deal.

01:24:26.660 --> 01:24:28.020
Steven is dead.

01:24:29.660 --> 01:24:30.660
What?

01:24:32.430 --> 01:24:37.830
I tried to tell you
but you would not answer my calls.

01:24:38.900 --> 01:24:40.030
How did it happen?

01:24:41.240 --> 01:24:47.370
Well, uh, he was in this, uh...

01:24:48.040 --> 01:24:51.380
He was in this house

01:24:51.550 --> 01:24:55.540
and, uh, he was covering a story

01:24:55.720 --> 01:24:59.720
on the, uh, women...

01:25:00.590 --> 01:25:02.890
The women's role in the war...

01:25:03.790 --> 01:25:08.530
And a hand grenade was thrown
through the window.

01:25:10.630 --> 01:25:13.000
Blown up in a whorehouse.

01:25:16.410 --> 01:25:21.940
When I heard, all I could think about

01:25:24.080 --> 01:25:31.680
was how glad I was
that it wasn't you.

01:25:33.720 --> 01:25:38.250
I'm sorry, I'm terribly sorry.
How are the kids taking it?

01:25:38.660 --> 01:25:40.290
Uh, ahem.

01:25:40.460 --> 01:25:44.900
Caroline is being very adult about it.

01:25:47.340 --> 01:25:49.930
David doesn't understand,

01:25:51.010 --> 01:25:56.610
and, uh, Linda is taking it
very, very badly.

01:25:56.780 --> 01:25:58.940
Anything I can do?

01:26:01.550 --> 01:26:03.820
May I tell Linda you wanna see her?

01:26:03.990 --> 01:26:05.790
Of course,
if you think it would do any good.

01:26:06.460 --> 01:26:08.360
I know it would.

01:26:09.490 --> 01:26:14.990
- I'll bring her tomorrow.
- No, no, not yet. Not here.

01:26:19.740 --> 01:26:23.500
- When are you coming home?
- I don't know.

01:26:25.640 --> 01:26:28.740
- A week, a month, a year?
- I don't know.

01:26:33.750 --> 01:26:35.510
Then I'll wait to hear from you.

01:26:37.650 --> 01:26:41.390
And just remember,
she won't be a little girl very long.

01:28:34.940 --> 01:28:36.870
- Mr. Wilson?
- Heh.

01:28:37.570 --> 01:28:39.010
What on earth are you doing?

01:28:39.180 --> 01:28:42.300
Just shut up
and get me a 7-foot sketch pad.

01:28:42.480 --> 01:28:44.670
- What?
- Go, go, go.

01:28:45.780 --> 01:28:50.220
Doctor. Doctor. Doctor.

01:29:03.270 --> 01:29:07.530
- Well, aren't you coming up with me?
- No, it's between the two of you.

01:29:07.700 --> 01:29:11.040
I'll pick you up by noon. Okay?

01:29:11.210 --> 01:29:16.510
- Do I have to?
- No, but I think you should.

01:29:32.300 --> 01:29:34.960
Oh, it's open, come in.

01:29:37.300 --> 01:29:38.960
It's Linda.

01:29:40.040 --> 01:29:41.560
Oh, uh...

01:29:41.740 --> 01:29:45.510
- Hi, Linda, heh, how are you?
- My mother made me come.

01:29:45.680 --> 01:29:46.700
What do you want?

01:29:48.880 --> 01:29:52.110
That's right, I forget. You're the one
that never beats around the bush.

01:29:52.280 --> 01:29:54.880
Okay, to talk about your father.

01:29:56.150 --> 01:30:02.090
Why? I didn't like him very much
if you wanna know.

01:30:02.260 --> 01:30:03.260
Oh.

01:30:03.830 --> 01:30:08.260
And he didn't like me either.
He was always going away.

01:30:08.430 --> 01:30:15.840
But he won't do it again
because he's dead. And I'm glad.

01:30:16.010 --> 01:30:17.300
What did you say?

01:30:18.410 --> 01:30:24.410
I said he's dead and I'm glad.

01:30:26.120 --> 01:30:28.560
You sound like a woodpecker
banging against a tree. You know:

01:30:29.950 --> 01:30:31.550
Stop that!

01:30:31.720 --> 01:30:39.130
You're just like him! You laugh too.
All men are like that.

01:30:40.100 --> 01:30:42.690
I don't care. I don't care.

01:30:42.870 --> 01:30:45.930
- Close that door, Linda.
- I'm going.

01:30:46.640 --> 01:30:50.330
If you go out of here now,
you'll stammer until your teeth fall out.

01:30:50.510 --> 01:30:51.910
I won't...

01:30:53.280 --> 01:30:54.570
Who can understand that?

01:30:54.740 --> 01:30:55.770
Stop that.

01:30:55.950 --> 01:30:58.390
Do you think someone is gonna
feel sorry for you, is that it?

01:30:58.550 --> 01:31:01.150
Rat-a-tat-tat-tat the rest of your life
like a stupid woodpecker?

01:31:01.320 --> 01:31:04.190
Don't say that.
Stop it, please. Stop it.

01:31:04.350 --> 01:31:07.470
I won't feel sorry for you. You might
as well start feeling sorry for yourself

01:31:07.620 --> 01:31:09.460
because nobody ever
stops stammering

01:31:09.630 --> 01:31:11.290
until they wanted
to stop stammering.

01:31:12.660 --> 01:31:16.530
Shut up, will you? Will you shut up?

01:31:20.670 --> 01:31:22.100
Sorry. I really am.

01:31:22.270 --> 01:31:24.970
I didn't mean to hit you,
honest, I didn't.

01:31:25.140 --> 01:31:27.270
Oh, yes, you did.

01:31:27.440 --> 01:31:28.440
Oh.

01:31:29.780 --> 01:31:31.660
I don't know if it was worth it,
but it worked.

01:31:32.620 --> 01:31:35.140
- What worked?
- You stopped stammering.

01:31:37.190 --> 01:31:38.210
Really?

01:31:41.590 --> 01:31:42.620
Up to a point.

01:31:42.790 --> 01:31:44.560
Are you sure you're all right?

01:31:44.730 --> 01:31:47.390
Oh, heh, fine.
I may never be the same.

01:31:47.560 --> 01:31:49.500
I'm just fine.

01:31:50.430 --> 01:31:54.130
- Do you see a 7-foot easel over there?
- Sure, right there.

01:31:54.300 --> 01:31:55.700
Uh-huh.

01:32:02.610 --> 01:32:04.740
- What's on it?
- A book.

01:32:05.680 --> 01:32:08.080
- A book?
- Yeah.

01:32:08.250 --> 01:32:11.220
It's a book that I promised
Howard Mann a long time ago

01:32:11.390 --> 01:32:13.860
but I never did get around
to finishing it

01:32:14.020 --> 01:32:15.790
until I got this idea
about your father.

01:32:15.960 --> 01:32:18.480
<i>- The Last Flower?</i>
- Yeah.

01:32:18.660 --> 01:32:20.490
That's about my father?

01:32:20.660 --> 01:32:26.470
Well, more about the way he thought,
why he always went away.

01:32:26.640 --> 01:32:30.770
- Why?
- Well, he knew something was wrong

01:32:30.940 --> 01:32:33.100
and he tried to fix it with his camera.

01:32:33.280 --> 01:32:37.150
In the end, you might say
he gave his life for an idea. Sort of.

01:32:39.850 --> 01:32:43.010
- What do you mean, "sort of"?
- The details don't...

01:32:43.190 --> 01:32:48.320
It's the thought that counts. It... Can
you read what's in the middle there?

01:32:51.030 --> 01:32:55.970
- "For Linda." For me?
- Yeah.

01:32:56.430 --> 01:33:01.130
"In the wistful hope that her world
will be better than mine."

01:33:02.040 --> 01:33:04.200
- I'm not sure I know what it means.
- Well, you will.

01:33:04.340 --> 01:33:05.470
Help me down with this.

01:33:11.850 --> 01:33:15.310
- Is that a picture of soldiers?
- Yes.

01:33:15.650 --> 01:33:17.090
- It's not very good.
- I know.

01:33:17.250 --> 01:33:20.120
Just read what it says, please.

01:33:20.290 --> 01:33:22.780
"World War XII,
as everybody knows,

01:33:22.960 --> 01:33:25.360
brought about the collapse
of civilization."

01:33:25.530 --> 01:33:27.790
Yeah, thanks.

01:33:30.570 --> 01:33:38.030
"Towns, cities and villages
disappeared from the Earth."

01:33:38.210 --> 01:33:43.700
- You mean everything was gone?
- Well, not exactly everything.

01:33:44.280 --> 01:33:46.610
There was one of these.

01:33:50.320 --> 01:33:53.080
Is that supposed to be a bird?

01:33:53.260 --> 01:33:55.350
If Michelangelo had you
looking over his shoulder,

01:33:55.530 --> 01:33:57.890
he never would have finished
that ceiling.

01:33:59.160 --> 01:34:04.460
As I was saying, "Towns, cities and
villages disappeared from the Earth.

01:34:04.630 --> 01:34:07.300
All the groves
and forests were destroyed.

01:34:08.100 --> 01:34:10.630
And all the gardens.
And all the works of art.

01:34:10.810 --> 01:34:11.810
Gee.

01:34:12.010 --> 01:34:15.640
Men, women and children
became lower than the lower animals.

01:34:15.810 --> 01:34:19.750
Emboldened by the pitiful condition
of the former lords of the Earth,

01:34:19.920 --> 01:34:21.580
rabbits descended upon them."

01:34:21.750 --> 01:34:23.240
Look out!

01:34:30.230 --> 01:34:32.590
It's okay now.

01:34:35.770 --> 01:34:39.330
The books, paintings, music
disappeared from the Earth.

01:34:39.500 --> 01:34:42.900
Human beings sat around,
just doing nothing.

01:34:43.070 --> 01:34:44.730
Years and years went by.

01:34:44.910 --> 01:34:46.710
Even the few generals
that were left

01:34:46.880 --> 01:34:49.610
had forgotten
what the last war decided.

01:34:50.410 --> 01:34:54.320
Boys and girls grew up
to stare at each other blankly.

01:34:54.480 --> 01:34:56.950
Love had passed from the Earth.

01:34:57.120 --> 01:35:00.680
- Well, what about sex?
- It was on its way out.

01:35:00.860 --> 01:35:05.730
But one day, a young girl
who had never seen a flower in her life

01:35:05.900 --> 01:35:08.660
chanced to come upon
the last one in the world.

01:35:08.830 --> 01:35:13.570
Well, she told the other human beings
that the last flower was dying

01:35:14.540 --> 01:35:16.940
and the only one
that would pay any attention to her

01:35:17.110 --> 01:35:19.630
was a young man
that she met wandering about.

01:35:20.440 --> 01:35:23.000
Do they have any clothes on?
I can't tell.

01:35:23.180 --> 01:35:25.170
If you can't tell,
what difference does it make?

01:35:25.350 --> 01:35:28.280
Anyway, the young man and the girl
nurtured the flower

01:35:28.450 --> 01:35:30.580
and it began to live again.

01:35:36.990 --> 01:35:41.660
One day, a bee visited the flower
and a humming bird.

01:35:44.130 --> 01:35:48.900
Before long there were two flowers,
and then four.

01:35:49.070 --> 01:35:50.970
Then a great many.

01:35:51.670 --> 01:35:56.010
And the young girl began to take
an interest in how she looked.

01:35:56.280 --> 01:35:59.680
- All of a sudden she's developed.
- It'll be your turn soon.

01:35:59.850 --> 01:36:05.220
The young man discovered
that touching the girl was pleasurable.

01:36:14.060 --> 01:36:15.090
Oh, uh...

01:36:23.470 --> 01:36:26.000
Love was reborn into the world.

01:36:26.610 --> 01:36:31.210
The children grew up strong and
healthy and learned to run and laugh.

01:36:34.380 --> 01:36:36.610
The dogs came out of their exile.

01:36:39.790 --> 01:36:44.660
The dogs are just like the rabbits.
Rabbits don't look much like rabbits.

01:36:44.830 --> 01:36:48.660
- I do the best I can.
- I know.

01:36:49.770 --> 01:36:53.330
The young man discovered,
by putting one stone upon the other,

01:36:53.500 --> 01:36:55.600
how to build a shelter.

01:36:55.770 --> 01:36:59.260
Pretty soon
everybody was building shelters.

01:36:59.440 --> 01:37:03.170
Towns, villages, cities sprang up.

01:37:05.310 --> 01:37:07.340
Song came back in the world.

01:37:12.590 --> 01:37:14.320
And troubadours and jugglers.

01:37:16.390 --> 01:37:17.720
Boy, he's pretty good.

01:37:21.000 --> 01:37:22.060
Butter fingers.

01:37:22.230 --> 01:37:27.190
And painters and poets
and sculptors and wheelwrights.

01:37:30.410 --> 01:37:32.100
- And soldiers.
- Uh-oh.

01:37:43.150 --> 01:37:49.020
And lieutenants, captains, generals,
major generals.

01:37:49.190 --> 01:37:51.790
And liberators.

01:37:57.370 --> 01:38:00.630
Excuse me. Sorry.

01:38:03.510 --> 01:38:06.810
Now, some people went one place
to live and some another.

01:38:06.980 --> 01:38:08.980
Before long,
those who went to live in the valleys

01:38:09.080 --> 01:38:10.880
wished they'd gone
to live in the hills.

01:38:11.050 --> 01:38:12.650
Those that had gone
to live in the hills

01:38:12.750 --> 01:38:14.110
wished they'd gone
to the valleys.

01:38:14.280 --> 01:38:16.310
What about those
who went to live on Long Island?

01:38:16.490 --> 01:38:18.080
They got what they deserved.

01:38:18.250 --> 01:38:24.520
The liberators, under the guidance
of God, set fire to the discontent.

01:38:24.690 --> 01:38:27.390
So presently,
the world was at war again.

01:38:39.280 --> 01:38:43.410
Only this time
the destruction was so complete,

01:38:43.580 --> 01:38:46.410
nothing at all was left in the world.

01:38:46.580 --> 01:38:51.890
- Nothing?
- Except one man.

01:38:53.160 --> 01:38:55.250
And one woman.

01:38:58.630 --> 01:39:00.490
And one flower.

01:39:06.840 --> 01:39:08.670
I like it.

01:39:09.340 --> 01:39:10.970
And I think I understand.

01:39:11.140 --> 01:39:14.670
Well, that's about all
anybody could ask about anything.

01:39:15.580 --> 01:39:17.740
Of course,
these drawings aren't very good.

01:39:17.910 --> 01:39:22.250
- Worse than usual?
- No, they've never been very good.

01:39:22.420 --> 01:39:25.080
Well, at least that's encouraging, heh.

01:39:25.250 --> 01:39:29.490
When are you coming home?
David misses you.

01:39:30.590 --> 01:39:32.820
I don't know.
Maybe when you stop doing that

01:39:33.000 --> 01:39:34.960
and I can learn
how to light somebody's cigarette

01:39:35.060 --> 01:39:37.230
without setting their head on fire.

01:39:40.340 --> 01:39:42.400
That's mother. I have to go.

01:39:43.570 --> 01:39:48.200
- Goodbye, Linda. Thanks for coming.
- Bye.

01:39:59.050 --> 01:40:01.520
Peter Piper
picked a peck of pickled peppers.

01:40:01.690 --> 01:40:05.490
If pickled peppers,

01:40:05.790 --> 01:40:09.490
where's the peck of pickled peppers
that Peter Piper picked?

01:40:22.880 --> 01:40:25.310
I don't have anything left
to give up for Lent.

01:40:25.480 --> 01:40:30.610
Nothing Norman Mailer has to say
is of the slightest interest to me.

01:40:30.790 --> 01:40:33.650
Howard, I've learned
not to mind being stared at.

01:40:33.820 --> 01:40:37.160
A little old lady helped me
across the street, I didn't even hit her.

01:40:38.560 --> 01:40:41.860
It seems like a very large
party for such a very small book.

01:40:42.030 --> 01:40:45.370
Well, here he is at last,
ladies and gentlemen, Peter Wilson.

01:40:46.100 --> 01:40:48.590
Peter, why don't you tell us a little bit
about how you work?

01:40:48.770 --> 01:40:50.970
- Uh, where that hidden well is.
- Well, I...

01:40:51.140 --> 01:40:54.010
How you get your inspiration
and all that stuff.

01:40:54.710 --> 01:40:57.810
I once knew a little girl
who stammered, but she stopped.

01:40:58.710 --> 01:41:02.210
- Now, what does that mean?
- Well, I don't know, but it helped me.

01:41:03.250 --> 01:41:07.350
Do you think your failing eyesight will be
a terrible handicap to you in the future?

01:41:08.290 --> 01:41:11.850
On the contrary, it's a godsend.
I can barely see you at all.

01:41:18.200 --> 01:41:20.360
You asked Terry to come here?
Now I am gonna kill you.

01:41:20.540 --> 01:41:22.470
I did not ask her, I swear.

01:41:22.640 --> 01:41:24.800
I talked to her,
but did not ask her in so many words.

01:41:24.940 --> 01:41:26.740
- How do you know?
- I heard her laughing.

01:41:26.910 --> 01:41:28.390
What's the matter with you,
you deaf?

01:41:28.540 --> 01:41:31.220
What's the matter with you, you
stupid? Why haven't you called her?

01:41:31.350 --> 01:41:33.030
Because
I've got to prove something first.

01:41:33.150 --> 01:41:34.950
- What?
- That I don't need her for anything.

01:41:35.050 --> 01:41:37.520
Otherwise she'll hold it
over my head for the rest of my life.

01:41:37.620 --> 01:41:39.820
I'll wait till the book is a success
and then call her.

01:41:39.920 --> 01:41:41.960
Well, if she had any sense at all,
she'd leave you.

01:41:42.090 --> 01:41:44.790
You won't be the only idiot
on the bestseller list, you know.

01:41:50.900 --> 01:41:54.390
There you are, Mr. Wilson,
you don't know how thrilled I am.

01:41:54.570 --> 01:41:56.730
Would you mind autographing
your book for me, please?

01:41:56.910 --> 01:41:58.350
Someday
it might be worth something.

01:41:58.510 --> 01:42:00.700
There's always
that slender chance, heh.

01:42:00.880 --> 01:42:04.240
Would you write, "To Helen McInness,
of Pittsburgh, PA"?

01:42:04.410 --> 01:42:06.210
Would you, please?

01:42:06.380 --> 01:42:08.750
- Would you do me a favor?
- Of course.

01:42:08.920 --> 01:42:13.050
Would you point me
to the nearest blank wall?

01:42:13.220 --> 01:42:18.160
- What?
- Find a wall and point me towards it.

01:42:18.330 --> 01:42:20.490
Well, there's one right over there.
You can't miss it.

01:42:20.600 --> 01:42:23.430
- Where?
- Right over there.

01:42:24.530 --> 01:42:26.260
Thanks, Helen.

01:42:43.120 --> 01:42:44.320
Hello.

01:42:53.860 --> 01:42:57.800
- What took you so long?
- I'm as stubborn as you are.

01:42:59.130 --> 01:43:00.800
- How's my drawing?
- Terrible.

01:43:03.510 --> 01:43:06.440
- Being obvious again.
- About what?

01:43:09.480 --> 01:43:12.180
I recognize the mating dance
when I see one.

01:43:13.920 --> 01:43:15.510
Come on.

01:43:21.520 --> 01:43:23.520
- You know what I like about you?
- What?

01:43:23.690 --> 01:43:25.160
You have absolutely no shame.

01:43:25.330 --> 01:43:27.230
- You know what I like about you?
- What?

01:43:27.400 --> 01:43:32.530
The operation didn't change you a bit.
You're still a mean, old son of a bitch.

